[ Whinnies ]

237
00:23:14,137 --> 00:23:16,537
[ Whimpering ]
No !

238
00:23:16,606 --> 00:23:18,836
- [ Grace ] No. Oh, God. No, no. Wait.
- [ Robert ] Grace.

239
00:23:18,909 --> 00:23:22,538
- No, Grace.
- No, no, no, no ! Leave me alone !

240
00:23:22,612 --> 00:23:25,706
Here. Grace.

241
00:23:25,782 --> 00:23:30,242
- Grace !
- Mr. MacLean, I'm so sorry.

242
00:23:33,857 --> 00:23:36,621
- Dad, why didn't you tell me ?
- I'm so sorry.

243
00:23:36,693 --> 00:23:39,321
[ Grace Crying ]

244
00:23:43,166 --> 00:23:48,627
You should have told her, Annie.
This animal is beyond help.

245
00:23:50,307 --> 00:23:53,743
Annie, can I have your permission now
to put him down ?

246
00:23:58,582 --> 00:24:00,982
No.

247
00:24:01,051 --> 00:24:02,484
[ Phone Ringing ]

248
00:24:02,552 --> 00:24:05,453
And get me every publication
on riding, racing, breeding.

249
00:24:05,522 --> 00:24:07,854
Everything.
Medical publications as well.

250
00:24:07,924 --> 00:24:11,451
Veterinarian journals.
And tell 'em it's me, and I want it now.

251
00:24:11,528 --> 00:24:15,123
- Hold on, hold on. Gottschalk.
- I'll call him back.

252
00:24:15,198 --> 00:24:17,598
- He's on his way to the airport--
- Lucy, I'll call him back.

253
00:24:17,667 --> 00:24:20,101
I'll call him back.
Just get me what I want.

254
00:24:57,541 --> 00:24:59,839
[ Annie's Voice ]
"A million years before man,

255
00:24:59,910 --> 00:25:03,368
"they grazed the vast
and empty plains,

256
00:25:03,446 --> 00:25:06,347
"living by voices
only they could hear.

257
00:25:08,218 --> 00:25:11,847
"They first came to know man
as the hunted knows the hunter,

258
00:25:17,994 --> 00:25:20,986
"for long before he used horses
for his labors,

259
00:25:23,333 --> 00:25:25,267
"he killed them for meat.

260
00:25:27,637 --> 00:25:30,606
"The alliance with man
would forever be fragile,

261
00:25:34,044 --> 00:25:37,309
"for the fear he'd struck
into their hearts...

262
00:25:37,380 --> 00:25:39,610
"was too deep to be dislodged.

263
00:25:41,818 --> 00:25:44,116
"Since that Neolithic moment,

264
00:25:44,187 --> 00:25:46,712
"when a horse
was first haltered,

265
00:25:47,991 --> 00:25:51,620
"there were those among men
who understood this.

266
00:25:53,163 --> 00:25:56,792
"They could see
into the creature's soul...

267
00:25:56,866 --> 00:25:59,733
"and soothe the wounds
they found there.

268
00:26:02,939 --> 00:26:07,342
"The secrets uttered softly
into troubled ears.

269
00:26:10,380 --> 00:26:14,214
These men were known
as the Whisperers."

270
00:26:19,689 --> 00:26:21,919
It's perfectly shot,
perfectly cropped,

271
00:26:21,992 --> 00:26:24,222
perfectly laid out,
and I am so bloody bored.

272
00:26:24,294 --> 00:26:26,558
Start again.

273
00:26:26,630 --> 00:26:30,464
Thank you. Would you excuse me
for one minute ?

274
00:26:30,533 --> 00:26:32,467
Yes.

275
00:26:34,738 --> 00:26:37,901
- Hello ?
- Yeah. This is Tom Booker.

276
00:26:37,974 --> 00:26:40,738
- I got a message you called.
- Oh, hello, Mr. Booker.

277
00:26:40,810 --> 00:26:42,903
It's Annie MacLean from Cover.

278
00:26:43,980 --> 00:26:45,971
You know, the magazine.

279
00:26:48,184 --> 00:26:50,311
Um, well, thank you
for returning my call--

280
00:26:50,387 --> 00:26:53,015
- Is there something I can do for you ?
- Yes, yes.

281
00:26:53,089 --> 00:26:57,082
I read this article about what you do
for people with horse problems.

282
00:26:57,160 --> 00:26:59,754
Well, the truth is, I help
horses with people problems.

283
00:26:59,829 --> 00:27:02,764
[ Chuckling ] Well, whichever way
you want to put it.

284
00:27:02,832 --> 00:27:07,462
Um, this article said that you were,
you were a, a horse whisperer.

285
00:27:07,537 --> 00:27:12,270
Oh, they said that, huh ?
A whisperer. Hmm.

286
00:27:12,342 --> 00:27:15,277
And I was hoping that
you'd come to New York...

287
00:27:15,345 --> 00:27:18,371
and take a look at my daughter's
horse and possibly do some--

288
00:27:18,448 --> 00:27:21,315
[ Chuckling ] Ma'am, I'm sorry, but I'm,
I'm afraid you've misunderstood...

289
00:27:21,384 --> 00:27:23,875
whatever it is you read
because that's not exactly what I do.

290
00:27:23,953 --> 00:27:27,719
-I mostly conduct clinics--
-Could you come to New York for the day?

291
00:27:27,791 --> 00:27:29,725
It's only a few hours by plane--

292
00:27:29,793 --> 00:27:32,091
And I'm not doin' them now.
I'm on my way to Montana.

293
00:27:32,162 --> 00:27:35,791
- I have a ranch to take care of.
- I'd pay your fare. Uh, first class.

294
00:27:35,865 --> 00:27:38,663
Ma'am, first class to Montana
is a waste of good money.

295
00:27:40,170 --> 00:27:42,866
Well, if you could just give me
a time when you'd be available.

296
00:27:42,939 --> 00:27:45,703
See, am l, am I being too polite
when I say "no" here in Nevada ?

297
00:27:45,775 --> 00:27:47,709
Does that mean "yes"
where you are ?

298
00:27:47,777 --> 00:27:50,371
I'm really sorry for your situation,
but there's nothin' I can do.

299
00:27:50,447 --> 00:27:52,108
You just called the wrong person.

300
00:27:52,182 --> 00:27:54,173
I'm sure there's some
fine horse doctors back east.

301
00:27:54,250 --> 00:27:56,445
No, but I don't want a horse doctor.
I want you.

302
00:27:56,519 --> 00:27:59,010
So I hope everything goes okay
with you and your horse.

303
00:27:59,089 --> 00:28:01,649
- Well, but, you see, it's not my horse.
- So, so, good-bye now.

304
00:28:01,725 --> 00:28:04,922
- [ Dial Tone ]
- [ Coins Clatter ]

305
00:28:09,132 --> 00:28:11,032
Grace ?

306
00:28:11,101 --> 00:28:13,399
Grace, it's Mom.

307
00:28:21,911 --> 00:28:24,471
Grace ?

308
00:28:24,547 --> 00:28:26,481
Grace ?

309
00:28:30,987 --> 00:28:33,751
Are you all right ?

310
00:28:41,965 --> 00:28:45,731
- I've decided about Pilgrim.
- Oh.

311
00:28:45,802 --> 00:28:49,329
I think we should
put him down.

312
00:28:49,406 --> 00:28:52,398
It's not fair
to let him suffer.

313
00:28:54,177 --> 00:28:56,680
- Well, I think that's a very--
- Maybe they should put me down too.

314
00:28:56,680 --> 00:28:57,840
- Well, I think that's a very--
- Maybe they should put me down too.

315
00:28:59,649 --> 00:29:02,982
- What ?
- I'm not much use anymore.

316
00:29:03,053 --> 00:29:05,544
[ Inhales ]

317
00:29:05,622 --> 00:29:09,558
- [ Machine Beeping ]
- You're getting a fax.

318
00:29:14,731 --> 00:29:17,666
[ Inhales ]

319
00:29:26,276 --> 00:29:28,210
You're up late.

320
00:29:28,278 --> 00:29:30,576
Is it ?

321
00:29:30,647 --> 00:29:32,342
- How was the dinner ?
- Is Grace asleep ?

322
00:29:32,415 --> 00:29:35,407
- Yeah, I think so.
- Nothing we haven't heard before.

323
00:29:35,485 --> 00:29:37,578
Just louder this time.
That's all.

324
00:29:38,855 --> 00:29:41,847
- So why'd you go ?
- One of us had to.

325
00:29:42,859 --> 00:29:45,419
They're still
our friends, Annie.

326
00:29:51,835 --> 00:29:53,769
Listen, I had a thought.

327
00:29:53,837 --> 00:29:56,863
What do you think we go
someplace warm, the three of us ?

328
00:29:56,940 --> 00:30:01,309
Bermuda or the Bahamas or--
What ?

329
00:30:04,514 --> 00:30:06,744
Mmm, nothing.

330
00:30:06,816 --> 00:30:08,875
No, I just don't know if Bermuda
would be such a good idea.

331
00:30:08,952 --> 00:30:11,785
Grace would have to wear
summer dresses or shorts.

332
00:30:11,855 --> 00:30:13,789
Oh, of course, of course.

333
00:30:18,728 --> 00:30:20,662
What is it ?

334
00:30:23,066 --> 00:30:27,662
I want to take Pilgrim out to see this
horse guy-- drive him out to Montana.

335
00:30:27,737 --> 00:30:30,137
- [ Laughs ]
- No, I'm serious.

336
00:30:30,206 --> 00:30:34,939
Wait. I thought you said you didn't
like the way he sounded on the phone.

337
00:30:35,011 --> 00:30:36,945
Well, I didn't.

338
00:30:37,013 --> 00:30:39,948
- I want to take Grace with me.
- You're kidding.

339
00:30:40,016 --> 00:30:42,746
Liz'll find me a trailer.
We can stay at motels along the way.

340
00:30:42,819 --> 00:30:45,515
- You made arrangements already ?
- No, I just checked out a few things.

341
00:30:45,588 --> 00:30:47,351
Wait a minute.
Drive a crazed horse--

342
00:30:47,423 --> 00:30:49,448
Oh, he's not crazed, Robert.
Don't exaggerate.

343
00:30:49,526 --> 00:30:52,290
- I just can't pack up and leave.
- I'm not asking you to. I'll do it.

344
00:30:52,362 --> 00:30:55,798
By yourself ? How ?
You can't take care of Pilgrim.

345
00:30:55,865 --> 00:30:58,425
He'll be sedated.
I do know a thing or two about horses.

346
00:30:58,501 --> 00:31:00,469
- What about the magazine ?
- I'm in charge.

347
00:31:00,537 --> 00:31:03,404
- I can oversee things from Montana.
- Oh, you're in charge.

348
00:31:03,473 --> 00:31:06,101
What about Grace ?
The doctor says she needs stability.

349
00:31:06,176 --> 00:31:08,041
I can't say he's being
all that effective with her.

350
00:31:08,111 --> 00:31:10,705
Are you a psychiatrist ?
He says it takes time.

351
00:31:10,780 --> 00:31:13,010
I don't care what he says !

352
00:31:13,082 --> 00:31:15,312
I cannot sit here and pretend
everything's gonna be all right.

353
00:31:15,385 --> 00:31:17,444
- I am not pretending. I am trusting--
- We have to do something !

354
00:31:17,520 --> 00:31:21,980
We are losing--
We are losing her !

355
00:31:22,058 --> 00:31:25,994
I don't care what the doctors say.
They don't know her.

356
00:31:26,062 --> 00:31:28,189
I don't care if this
doesn't sound rational.

357
00:31:28,264 --> 00:31:30,289
Nobody is suggesting anything better !

358
00:31:31,935 --> 00:31:34,904
I, I can't explain it, Robert.
I just have this feeling.

359
00:31:34,971 --> 00:31:37,337
I just know
it's the right thing.

360
00:31:38,408 --> 00:31:40,342
Why, Annie ?

361
00:31:46,416 --> 00:31:48,350
I just know it.

362
00:31:54,090 --> 00:31:58,083
Does this, uh, cowboy vet
know that you're coming ?

363
00:31:59,295 --> 00:32:01,229
Yeah.

364
00:32:07,003 --> 00:32:11,167
- What if Grace doesn't wanna go ?
- She will if you think she should.

365
00:32:14,611 --> 00:32:16,545
And you think it's best
if I don't come.

366
00:32:16,613 --> 00:32:19,776
- No, that's not what I said.
- Daddy ?

367
00:32:22,619 --> 00:32:24,553
I don't wanna go.

368
00:32:25,622 --> 00:32:27,453
Straight back. Come on.

369
00:32:27,523 --> 00:32:29,514
- A little closer. A little more.
- [ Pilgrim Whinnying ]

370
00:32:29,592 --> 00:32:32,083
Watch it.
Get behind him.

371
00:32:34,197 --> 00:32:37,132
- [ Whinnying Continues ]
- [ Man #1 ] Hold it. Get back !

372
00:32:37,200 --> 00:32:39,191
- [ Man #2 ] Watch it !
- [ Man #1 ] There he goes, Eddie !

373
00:32:39,269 --> 00:32:42,898
-Why don't you get inside and--
-[ Man #1 ] We're doing the best we can!

374
00:32:42,972 --> 00:32:46,408
It's the only way to load
this kind of horse. [ Yells ]

375
00:32:46,476 --> 00:32:48,876
Keep trying !

376
00:32:48,945 --> 00:32:52,312
- We should give him another sedative.
- We did.

377
00:32:52,382 --> 00:32:55,146
- [ Whinnies ]
- Get the gate ! Get the gate !

378
00:32:55,218 --> 00:32:58,085
Get out of here !
Hold that door !

379
00:32:58,154 --> 00:33:00,213
- [ Men Yelling ]
- [ Snorting ]

380
00:33:04,527 --> 00:33:07,462
You got a gun, just in case ?

381
00:33:07,530 --> 00:33:09,464
Of course not.

382
00:33:09,532 --> 00:33:11,466
That's probably best.

383
00:33:11,534 --> 00:33:14,970
You may want to shoot yourself
halfway to Ohio.

384
00:33:16,306 --> 00:33:19,241
 [ Electronic ]

385
00:33:39,929 --> 00:33:42,363
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

386
00:33:48,938 --> 00:33:50,963
[ Truck Engine Revving ]

387
00:33:57,013 --> 00:33:58,810
[ Revving Continues ]

388
00:34:10,426 --> 00:34:13,327
- [ Whinnies ]
- [ Truck Horn Honking ]

389
00:34:13,396 --> 00:34:15,523
[ Whinnying Continues ]

390
00:34:25,541 --> 00:34:28,533
Grace, are you hungry ?
Do you want to stop for lunch ?

391
00:34:28,611 --> 00:34:30,545
I don't care.

392
00:34:33,149 --> 00:34:37,643
I want to find a place before
it gets dark. What do you think ?

393
00:34:37,720 --> 00:34:41,053
- Grace.
- Doesn't matter.

394
00:34:42,125 --> 00:34:44,286
Okay, listen up.
This is what I'll do:

395
00:34:44,360 --> 00:34:46,225
I'll get to the next motel,
see if they have a fax--

396
00:34:46,295 --> 00:34:49,560
-[ Thumping ]
-[Annie Gasps ] Oh, wait. Hang on. Uh--

397
00:34:49,632 --> 00:34:51,691
I gotta go, okay ?
Later.

398
00:34:55,471 --> 00:34:57,701
 [ Muffled ]

399
00:34:57,774 --> 00:35:01,232
Grace, do you wanna put
your music on up here ?

400
00:35:04,781 --> 00:35:07,147
[ Muffled ]
Grace.

401
00:35:08,718 --> 00:35:11,744
Do you want to put
your music on up here ?

402
00:35:17,960 --> 00:35:20,360
[ Man #1 On Radio ] And when you
purchase your Eureka World Deluxe Vac--

403
00:35:20,430 --> 00:35:24,230
[ Man #2 ] Near the agricultural
markets, and farm news headlines--

404
00:35:24,300 --> 00:35:26,234
[ Man #3 On Radio ]
lnsecticide for small grains.

405
00:35:26,302 --> 00:35:28,361
Important to always read
and follow label instructions--

406
00:35:28,438 --> 00:35:31,874
[ Man #4 On Radio ] This here man was
rejuvenated in the grace of the Lord.

407
00:35:31,941 --> 00:35:35,934
- He was washed.
-  [ Country ]

408
00:35:41,751 --> 00:35:45,710
Mmm, Grace, look at this.

409
00:35:47,790 --> 00:35:50,918
Do you wanna see that ?

410
00:35:50,993 --> 00:35:54,224
- I don't care.
- [ Mocking ] I don't care.

411
00:35:55,465 --> 00:35:57,399
Oh, it'll be fun.

412
00:35:57,467 --> 00:36:01,870
You haven't see any
of the sights yet. It's history.

413
00:36:01,938 --> 00:36:04,702
When I was 13, I used to love
doing things like this.

414
00:36:04,774 --> 00:36:07,743
Well, you were never 13, Mom.

415
00:36:14,050 --> 00:36:15,940
Oh.

416
00:36:21,745 --> 00:36:24,270
Great idea, Mom. Now what ?

417
00:36:24,348 --> 00:36:27,749
[ Sighs ]
How long is this gonna go on ?

418
00:36:27,818 --> 00:36:31,447
- What ?
- You know what I mean.

419
00:36:37,695 --> 00:36:39,856
Do you want us to go back home ?
ls that what you want ?

420
00:36:39,930 --> 00:36:41,363
What are you asking me for ?

421
00:36:41,432 --> 00:36:43,059
You didn't ask me if I wanted
to come in the first place.

422
00:36:43,133 --> 00:36:45,033
Now I get to decide ?
Sorry.

423
00:36:46,537 --> 00:36:49,028
Do you know
who I'm doing this for ?

424
00:36:49,106 --> 00:36:51,040
- I'm doing this for you.
- Bullshit !

425
00:36:51,108 --> 00:36:54,168
It's all about you-- about you deciding,
about you being right !

426
00:36:54,244 --> 00:36:56,337
-It's like we work for you or something!
-I don't believe this !

427
00:36:56,413 --> 00:36:59,041
- How come Daddy didn't come, huh ?
- What do you mean ?

428
00:36:59,116 --> 00:37:01,880
You know everything.
You figure it out.

429
00:37:01,952 --> 00:37:04,978
- Your father had to work.
- Yeah, right.

430
00:37:05,055 --> 00:37:07,489
Please stop acting like you know
what you're talking about.

431
00:37:07,558 --> 00:37:09,321
You are amazing, you know ?

432
00:37:09,393 --> 00:37:12,123
I mean, you act like I don't
even live in that house anymore.

433
00:37:12,196 --> 00:37:14,926
You think I don't know what's going on ?
You think I'm still five years old.

434
00:37:14,999 --> 00:37:17,399
- When you act like this, you are.
- How long are we gonna be away, huh ?

435
00:37:17,468 --> 00:37:20,596
- I don't know. I don't know.
- What if this guy can't do anything ?

436
00:37:20,671 --> 00:37:22,605
I don't know !

437
00:37:24,008 --> 00:37:26,238
I don't have all the answers.

438
00:37:26,310 --> 00:37:29,006
No, you just act like you do.

439
00:38:29,239 --> 00:38:31,673
[ Crying ]

440
00:39:07,578 --> 00:39:11,878
- You okay, ma'am ?
- Yeah, I'm, I'm fine.

441
00:39:11,949 --> 00:39:14,816
[ Ranger ] That young lady's
gettin' a little worried.

442
00:39:14,885 --> 00:39:17,319
Oh, sorry. Sorry.

443
00:39:24,828 --> 00:39:27,262
- Good night, ma'am.
- Good night.

444
00:39:30,134 --> 00:39:33,069
[ Beeping ]

445
00:39:36,373 --> 00:39:39,103
- You buckled up ?
- Mm-hmm.

446
00:39:40,277 --> 00:39:43,337
- Are you cold ?
- A little.

447
00:39:52,856 --> 00:39:54,824
[ Man #5 On Radio ] You may have
seen the Kennel Club champion...

448
00:39:54,892 --> 00:39:57,827
being rewarded with a box
of chocolates the other day.

449
00:39:57,895 --> 00:39:59,829
Veterinarians and humane--

450
00:39:59,897 --> 00:40:03,799
[ Woman ]  But I can't
get you out of my mind 

451
00:40:03,867 --> 00:40:05,801
[ Woman On Radio ]
Winter weather got you down ?

452
00:40:05,869 --> 00:40:09,999
Wilson Travel is offering charter
packages to sunny Orlando, Florida.

453
00:40:10,073 --> 00:40:12,598
[ Man #6 On Radio ] Well, looks like
lots of precipitation, overnight.

454
00:40:12,676 --> 00:40:15,770
Rainfall an inch and a half. Plus,
it looks like another half an inch--

455
00:40:15,846 --> 00:40:17,780
[ Man #7 On Radio ]
He had an epiphany.

456
00:40:17,848 --> 00:40:20,180
Paul had been transformed
by the grace of God,

457
00:40:20,250 --> 00:40:22,582
so he was a new creation
in Christ.

458
00:40:22,653 --> 00:40:24,587
He said the man
was completely--

459
00:40:24,655 --> 00:40:27,089
[ Man #8 On Radio ] Up from down
in the Northern Plains, John Deere.

460
00:40:27,157 --> 00:40:29,091
We're glad to see you.

461
00:40:36,200 --> 00:40:39,192
[ Grace ]
Gee, this place looks like fun.

462
00:40:43,307 --> 00:40:45,366
Don't they believe in signs
around here ?

463
00:40:45,442 --> 00:40:49,776
What would they say ? "Ten miles to Big
Rock, twenty miles to Bigger Rock" ?

464
00:40:49,846 --> 00:40:52,713
- No.
- Great trip. I'm having so much fun.

465
00:40:52,783 --> 00:40:55,115
I think I should turn here.

466
00:40:55,185 --> 00:40:58,245
[ Grace ] Oh, yeah. Those rocks
