01:29:12,852 --> 01:29:15,412
Nice. Real nice.

947
01:29:15,488 --> 01:29:18,423
Now there's a little road
up at the end here. Turn onto it.

948
01:29:23,463 --> 01:29:26,261
Now just follow this.
Nothing to it.

949
01:29:27,600 --> 01:29:30,865
I'm gonna kinda close my eyes
here for a little while,

950
01:29:30,937 --> 01:29:33,838
so keep goin'
till you run out of road.

951
01:29:33,907 --> 01:29:36,899
Uh, l, l,
I don't think I can.

952
01:29:36,976 --> 01:29:39,171
It's not a question if you can.
You are.

953
01:29:57,497 --> 01:29:59,931
[ Tom ] Where did you get
Pilgrim from ?

954
01:29:59,999 --> 01:30:04,599
We bought him in Kentucky. Me and my mom
took a trip down there to see him.

955
01:30:04,732 --> 01:30:07,326
That must have been special.

956
01:30:07,402 --> 01:30:09,336
Yeah.

957
01:30:13,975 --> 01:30:15,909
Are you afraid of anything,

958
01:30:15,977 --> 01:30:17,911
Tom Booker ?

959
01:30:20,949 --> 01:30:22,883
Oh, growin' old.

960
01:30:22,951 --> 01:30:24,885
Not bein' much use.

961
01:30:30,692 --> 01:30:33,024
- Hey, Grace ?
- Hmm ?

962
01:30:33,094 --> 01:30:35,187
What went on out there
with Pilgrim ?

963
01:30:44,572 --> 01:30:47,097
See, Grace, I got a problem.

964
01:30:47,175 --> 01:30:51,942
When I work with a horse,
I like to know its history.

965
01:30:52,013 --> 01:30:55,449
Most of the times a horse, in its
own way, can tell you the whole story,

966
01:30:55,517 --> 01:30:59,510
but sometimes they get so messed up in
their head that you need more to go on.

967
01:31:00,855 --> 01:31:02,880
Now I don't know how you feel
about talkin' about it,

968
01:31:02,957 --> 01:31:05,619
and if you don't feel like it,
I understand,

969
01:31:06,995 --> 01:31:10,954
but if I'm gonna figure out
what's goin' on in his head,

970
01:31:12,567 --> 01:31:16,503
sure would help me if I understood
exactly what happened that day.

971
01:31:24,412 --> 01:31:28,473
You know, not today.
Whenever you feel like it.

972
01:31:28,550 --> 01:31:31,383
I'll leave that up to you.

973
01:31:44,465 --> 01:31:46,399
Uh-oh.

974
01:31:50,872 --> 01:31:53,841
- The answer's no.
- You haven't heard the question yet.

975
01:31:53,908 --> 01:31:56,001
Now, the truth is, you'd be
doin' me a real favor.

976
01:31:56,077 --> 01:31:58,602
I got all these young colts
that need ridin'.

977
01:31:58,680 --> 01:32:01,615
Rimrock here, he's--
I mean, he's feelin' kind of left out.

978
01:32:01,683 --> 01:32:03,776
Poor thing.

979
01:32:03,851 --> 01:32:08,413
He'd be grateful, and he'd
take real good care with you.

980
01:32:08,489 --> 01:32:12,289
[ Sighs ] ls this how you're gonna
make me pay my phone bill ?

981
01:32:12,360 --> 01:32:14,521
No. No, ma'am.

982
01:32:14,596 --> 01:32:17,360
That part's extra.

983
01:32:22,837 --> 01:32:25,499
Oh, brought you a hat.

984
01:32:25,573 --> 01:32:29,270
- Oh, I have a hat.
- I know. I've seen it.

985
01:32:37,185 --> 01:32:39,551
I think my stirrups
are too long or--

986
01:32:39,621 --> 01:32:41,885
- No, they're fine. Relax your center.
- Yeah.

987
01:32:41,956 --> 01:32:44,322
- Just sittin' in a bucket.
- Well, it's all coming back, you know.

988
01:32:44,392 --> 01:32:46,383
I mean, I'll be fine.

989
01:32:46,461 --> 01:32:49,897
Okay, well, then
I'll stop talkin' then.

990
01:32:49,964 --> 01:32:53,229
No, I didn't mean that. I-- You know,
I've never ridden western before.

991
01:32:53,301 --> 01:32:56,361
Yeah, but he doesn't know that.
Just sit the horse.

992
01:32:56,437 --> 01:32:59,031
You have a nice seat,
and you're doing fine.

993
01:32:59,107 --> 01:33:01,041
Thank you.

994
01:33:10,151 --> 01:33:12,585
[ Whinnying ]

995
01:33:15,623 --> 01:33:17,557
[ Grunts, Giggles ]

996
01:33:17,625 --> 01:33:19,718
- You look good. You feel okay ?
- Yeah.

997
01:33:19,794 --> 01:33:22,092
- Wanna pick it up a little ?
- Yeah.

998
01:33:27,669 --> 01:33:29,933
Watch your reins.

999
01:33:30,004 --> 01:33:32,472
Give him some room.
Let him do the work.

1000
01:33:59,200 --> 01:34:01,964
- Okay ? You okay ?
- Yep.

1001
01:34:02,036 --> 01:34:04,231
Let's go.

1002
01:34:55,857 --> 01:34:57,791
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

1003
01:35:21,237 --> 01:35:23,171
I envy your mother.

1004
01:35:25,574 --> 01:35:28,338
I do.

1005
01:35:30,379 --> 01:35:33,507
It must be great
to be her age...

1006
01:35:33,582 --> 01:35:38,042
and to be at that point in life
when you have no more guesswork.

1007
01:35:40,056 --> 01:35:43,287
No more impossible decisions
to make.

1008
01:35:43,359 --> 01:35:46,294
And anyway, it doesn't matter
because all the worries...

1009
01:35:46,362 --> 01:35:49,593
and all the wrong turns that
you made are as valuable and as,

1010
01:35:49,665 --> 01:35:54,568
as, as cherished as the things
that you did right.

1011
01:35:54,637 --> 01:35:57,071
[ Sighs ]
Must be such a relief.

1012
01:35:59,642 --> 01:36:02,304
Must be such peace in that.

1013
01:36:04,380 --> 01:36:09,340
I don't think you have to wait to be
her age to find that kind of peace.

1014
01:36:09,418 --> 01:36:12,819
Yeah, but how would you know,
unless it was all behind you ?

1015
01:36:12,888 --> 01:36:14,913
- Do you have it ?
- Sometimes.

1016
01:36:14,990 --> 01:36:16,924
Not all the time,
but sometimes.

1017
01:36:16,992 --> 01:36:19,085
When ?

1018
01:36:19,161 --> 01:36:21,095
Wakin' up on the ranch
in the morning,

1019
01:36:21,163 --> 01:36:23,961
knowin' what
I'm supposed to do that day.

1020
01:36:24,033 --> 01:36:25,967
Knowing I'm home.

1021
01:36:26,035 --> 01:36:29,198
Hmm.

1022
01:36:29,271 --> 01:36:32,900
I wake up every morning,
and I don't know a damn thing. Was l--

1023
01:36:32,975 --> 01:36:35,842
[ Sighs ]

1024
01:36:35,911 --> 01:36:38,402
Was I right to bring her here,
away from what's familiar--

1025
01:36:38,481 --> 01:36:42,212
away from her father,
her friends ?

1026
01:36:42,284 --> 01:36:46,778
And the more I try and fix things,
the more everything falls apart.

1027
01:36:46,856 --> 01:36:48,881
Maybe you should
let 'em fall.

1028
01:36:51,894 --> 01:36:53,828
No, I can't.

1029
01:36:55,197 --> 01:36:57,131
Why ?

1030
01:37:09,812 --> 01:37:11,746
Do you think
I was right to come ?

1031
01:37:11,814 --> 01:37:14,578
I can't answer that, Annie.

1032
01:37:15,784 --> 01:37:18,514
Hmm. Well,
I'll know soon enough.

1033
01:37:18,587 --> 01:37:21,488
If I've made a mistake,
Grace will let me know.

1034
01:37:22,558 --> 01:37:24,492
She's a strong kid.

1035
01:37:25,694 --> 01:37:27,719
She gets that from somebody.

1036
01:37:29,431 --> 01:37:31,365
Hmm.

1037
01:37:37,773 --> 01:37:40,571
Thank you for all you're doing.

1038
01:37:40,643 --> 01:37:43,544
You and your family--
Ietting us stay at the house.

1039
01:37:43,612 --> 01:37:45,546
It wasn't gettin' much use.

1040
01:37:50,152 --> 01:37:52,086
What was your wife like ?

1041
01:37:54,823 --> 01:37:56,757
She had reddish hair.

1042
01:37:56,825 --> 01:37:59,589
Not, not quite. Almost.

1043
01:37:59,662 --> 01:38:01,562
Depended on the light.

1044
01:38:02,798 --> 01:38:04,732
She had green eyes.

1045
01:38:06,101 --> 01:38:09,161
And when she played,
that was it.

1046
01:38:10,739 --> 01:38:13,640
Somethin' just went
right through me.

1047
01:38:13,709 --> 01:38:16,439
I'd never heard music
like that played before.

1048
01:38:18,714 --> 01:38:21,148
And the way she looked
when she played it.

1049
01:38:24,019 --> 01:38:27,420
And then one day, she looked at me
that way, and that was it--

1050
01:38:27,489 --> 01:38:30,617
- [ Chuckles ]
- for both of us.

1051
01:38:34,897 --> 01:38:38,492
I knew she didn't want to be a rancher's
wife, but I wanted to give it a try.

1052
01:38:38,567 --> 01:38:43,504
I thought she could give music lessons
to the kids in town-- the school--

1053
01:38:43,572 --> 01:38:47,633
and that our kids would grow up with
my brother's kids and play together.

1054
01:38:50,412 --> 01:38:53,745
But...
she wasn't happy here.

1055
01:38:53,816 --> 01:38:56,250
"Too much space," she said.

1056
01:38:57,319 --> 01:38:59,310
So why didn't you stay
in Chicago ?

1057
01:39:00,556 --> 01:39:02,490
Wasn't enough space.

1058
01:39:04,827 --> 01:39:07,455
It just wasn't meant to be.

1059
01:39:10,332 --> 01:39:13,130
But how did you know...
for sure ?

1060
01:39:13,202 --> 01:39:17,662
Knowing's the easy part.
Sayin' it out loud is the hard part.

1061
01:39:21,577 --> 01:39:25,513
Mmm. Seems so obvious now,
doesn't it ?

1062
01:39:25,581 --> 01:39:28,482
"We weren't right for each other.
If only we knew then."

1063
01:39:28,550 --> 01:39:31,542
I didn't love her
'cause it was right.

1064
01:39:31,620 --> 01:39:33,554
I just loved her.

1065
01:39:49,071 --> 01:39:52,837
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

1066
01:40:09,458 --> 01:40:14,157
For whatever it's worth, Annie, it took
a lot of guts for you to come here.

1067
01:40:20,836 --> 01:40:22,531
Lift your leg.

1068
01:41:07,416 --> 01:41:09,350
[ Sighs ]

1069
01:41:11,019 --> 01:41:15,046
[ Horses Whinnying, Snorting ]

1070
01:41:34,504 --> 01:41:37,564
- [ Cow Mooing ]
- [ Moos ]

1071
01:41:37,640 --> 01:41:39,608
[ Whistles ]
Come on. Come on.

1072
01:41:39,676 --> 01:41:42,577
[ Mooing ]

1073
01:41:44,748 --> 01:41:47,012
[ Grace ]
Hey, Joe.

1074
01:41:47,083 --> 01:41:49,779
Hi.

1075
01:41:49,853 --> 01:41:52,253
Would you let me
ride your horse ?

1076
01:41:57,360 --> 01:41:59,453
Have you talked
to Tom about it ?

1077
01:41:59,529 --> 01:42:02,089
Of course I have.

1078
01:42:02,165 --> 01:42:04,633
I don't know.

1079
01:42:04,701 --> 01:42:06,692
You sure Tom said
it's all right ?

1080
01:42:06,770 --> 01:42:10,365
- You gonna give me a hand or what ?
- You sure ?

1081
01:42:10,440 --> 01:42:13,238
Come on !

1082
01:42:13,309 --> 01:42:15,800
Okay.

1083
01:42:15,879 --> 01:42:18,143
Easy. Hold it.

1084
01:42:18,214 --> 01:42:22,651
Okay.
[ Sighs, Grunts ]

1085
01:42:24,287 --> 01:42:25,948
- [ Horse Snorts ]
- Whoa.

1086
01:42:26,022 --> 01:42:29,082
[ Grunts ]
Got it. Got it.

1087
01:42:29,159 --> 01:42:31,093
I can do it.

1088
01:42:33,062 --> 01:42:34,825
Here.

1089
01:42:36,866 --> 01:42:38,800
[ Whinnies ]

1090
01:42:38,868 --> 01:42:40,426
Are you okay ?

1091
01:42:51,981 --> 01:42:54,609
[ Giggling ]

1092
01:42:54,684 --> 01:42:59,121
Hey ! You better not
say anything !

1093
01:42:59,189 --> 01:43:01,123
[ Blows Raspberry ]

1094
01:43:01,257 --> 01:43:04,124
[ Frogs Chirping ]

1095
01:43:17,607 --> 01:43:19,131
[ Giggling ]

1096
01:43:25,682 --> 01:43:29,618
I thought there were
too many forks, so I just, um--

1097
01:43:29,686 --> 01:43:33,349
[ Whispers ]
Oh, you look really pretty.

1098
01:43:33,423 --> 01:43:35,357
Thanks.

1099
01:43:45,001 --> 01:43:47,060
Does anybody want
something to drink ?

1100
01:43:47,136 --> 01:43:49,570
- [ Pan Clattering ]
- [ Annie ] Shit !

1101
01:43:49,639 --> 01:43:51,698
- [ Giggling ]
- Shh !

1102
01:43:52,909 --> 01:43:57,744
- I better go give your mom a hand.
- Oh, yeah.

1103
01:43:57,814 --> 01:44:03,309
- Everything under control here ?
- Um, no, not really.

1104
01:44:03,386 --> 01:44:05,946
Uh, it's been so long
since I've done this.

1105
01:44:06,022 --> 01:44:09,082
I've forgotten. And I couldn't
find any Parmesan cheese.

1106
01:44:09,158 --> 01:44:11,524
Well, you got an easy crowd
out there as long as it's hot.

1107
01:44:11,594 --> 01:44:13,528
Can I do anything ?

1108
01:44:13,596 --> 01:44:16,030
Uh, just make yourself
comfortable.

1109
01:44:16,099 --> 01:44:18,033
I am comfortable.

1110
01:44:18,101 --> 01:44:22,060
Well, um, in that case,
you can bring in the... pasta.

1111
01:44:22,138 --> 01:44:24,902
You missed a button.

1112
01:44:24,974 --> 01:44:27,340
Thank you.

1113
01:44:32,682 --> 01:44:36,049
You know, I'll have another round
of that spaghetti, if I may.

1114
01:44:36,119 --> 01:44:39,486
- Oh, of course.
- [ Frank ] Thank you.

1115
01:44:39,556 --> 01:44:42,116
I, uh, like the sauce.
Maybe I could get the recipe ?

1116
01:44:42,191 --> 01:44:45,092
It's from a jar.

1117
01:44:45,161 --> 01:44:47,994
Oh.

1118
01:44:49,332 --> 01:44:52,631
Well, now, you know what.

1119
01:44:52,702 --> 01:44:55,603
I, uh, used jar sauce once.

1120
01:44:55,672 --> 01:44:57,936
I don't believe
it was near as good as this.

1121
01:44:58,007 --> 01:45:00,271
- Isn't that right, Frank ?
- No.

1122
01:45:00,343 --> 01:45:03,938
No. You know, I think you gotta know
which brand to pick.

1123
01:45:04,013 --> 01:45:06,140
I sure would like
the name of this one.

1124
01:45:06,215 --> 01:45:08,706
Mm-hmm.

1125
01:45:08,785 --> 01:45:11,618
Annie, you've given me
a rare night off.

1126
01:45:11,688 --> 01:45:15,283
Ooh, you're touchin'
on a sore subject here.

1127
01:45:15,358 --> 01:45:20,057
Diane's got these big dreams in her head
about gettin' away to-- What was it ?

1128
01:45:20,129 --> 01:45:22,063
- Greece, Morocco ?
- Morocco.

1129
01:45:22,131 --> 01:45:24,622
[ Frank ] One of these places
where women wear masks...

1130
01:45:24,701 --> 01:45:27,067
and everybody's runnin'
around in robes and--

1131
01:45:27,136 --> 01:45:29,434
[ Diane ]
Well, we could use a vacation.

1132
01:45:29,505 --> 01:45:31,473
Well, we're goin'
to Branson for the wedding.

1133
01:45:31,541 --> 01:45:33,668
-You just had a turn.
-You don't know how to play these games.

1134
01:45:33,743 --> 01:45:35,074
- Hey !
- Yes, I do.

1135
01:45:35,144 --> 01:45:37,806
- You do not.
- You know, Frank.

1136
01:45:37,880 --> 01:45:41,509
You know, Branson, Missouri,
is not exactly Morocco.

1137
01:45:41,584 --> 01:45:43,575
[ Frank ]
I got family there.

1138
01:45:43,653 --> 01:45:47,316
Got no family in Morocco
as far as I know.

1139
01:45:47,390 --> 01:45:48,322
- It's my turn.
- You had a turn.

1140
01:45:48,391 --> 01:45:49,449
- It was not !
- Was so !

1141
01:45:49,525 --> 01:45:52,517
- Settle down.
- You're just showin' off for--

1142
01:45:52,595 --> 01:45:54,529
- [ Joe ] Shut up, stupid.
- You're the only one who's stupid.

1143
01:45:54,597 --> 01:45:56,861
[ Twin ] Lettin' her go
and fall off your horse.

1144
01:45:56,933 --> 01:45:58,161
[ Joe ]
You little turd.

1145
01:45:58,234 --> 01:46:00,702
[ Twin ] I saw them.
Her tryin' to get on Gonzo.

1146
01:46:00,770 --> 01:46:03,295
- You turd !
- Joe !

1147
01:46:03,373 --> 01:46:05,841
- Did you go riding ?
- [ Twin ] No !

1148
01:46:05,908 --> 01:46:08,536
- [ Frank ] Get up off the floor.
- [ Diane ] Out you go. Now !

1149
01:46:08,611 --> 01:46:12,172
- [ Joe ] I didn't start it.
- [ Diane ] Right now. Come on.

1150
01:46:12,248 --> 01:46:15,012
Annie, I'm so sorry.
They're just tired.

1151
01:46:15,084 --> 01:46:17,644
We should get them home to bed.
Say good night and thank you.

1152
01:46:17,720 --> 01:46:20,655
- Annie, dinner was delicious.
- Thank you so much.

1153
01:46:20,723 --> 01:46:23,214
- Say thank you.
- Thank you.

1154
01:46:23,292 --> 01:46:25,385
Joe, did Grace try to ride ?

1155
01:46:25,461 --> 01:46:28,362
I expect you should talk
to Grace about that, ma'am.

1156
01:46:28,431 --> 01:46:31,025
If I did anything wrong,
I'm sorry.

1157
01:46:31,100 --> 01:46:33,034
Mm-hmm.

1158
01:46:34,537 --> 01:46:36,903
Don't let her turn you away.

1159
01:47:15,111 --> 01:47:17,045
[ Knocking ]

1160
01:47:19,649 --> 01:47:21,583
Grace.

1161
01:47:23,019 --> 01:47:25,681
Is everything all right ?

1162
01:47:28,691 --> 01:47:32,718
- Did you try riding again ?
- Yeah.

1163
01:47:32,795 --> 01:47:34,695
Does that mean I'm cured ?

1164
01:47:37,834 --> 01:47:39,768
Nobody's trying to cure you.

1165
01:47:45,241 --> 01:47:49,302
Look, I just wanna say I think
it's great that you're riding again.

1166
01:47:52,315 --> 01:47:54,249
And I think I know why
you needed to--

1167
01:47:54,317 --> 01:47:56,308
Yeah, you know everything.

1168
01:47:57,987 --> 01:48:00,888
Stop it. Why won't you
let me talk to you ?

1169
01:48:00,957 --> 01:48:03,619
Why are you
so angry with me ?

1170
01:48:03,693 --> 01:48:06,287
Whatever I do, it's wrong.
Whatever I say, it's wrong.

1171
01:48:06,362 --> 01:48:08,990
Yeah ? Well, now
you know how it feels.

1172
01:48:10,199 --> 01:48:12,997
Look, I know that
I'm hard on you sometimes.

1173
01:48:13,069 --> 01:48:16,129
- Right !
- Sorry if that makes you feel this way.

1174
01:48:16,205 --> 01:48:17,900
But if I push you,
it's only because--

1175
01:48:17,974 --> 01:48:20,670
Because if I'm your perfect daughter,
that makes you the perfect mother ?

1176
01:48:20,743 --> 01:48:25,442
I don't deserve that !
I don't push for me.

1177
01:48:25,515 --> 01:48:28,951
I push for you so that
you don't spend half your life...

1178
01:48:29,018 --> 01:48:30,315
not knowing where you belong.

1179
01:48:30,386 --> 01:48:32,911
Yeah ? Well,
you've done a great job.

1180
01:48:34,557 --> 01:48:36,923
Yeah.

1181
01:48:36,993 --> 01:48:39,086
[ Sobbing ]

1182
01:48:44,901 --> 01:48:49,998
Who's ever gonna
want me like this ?

1183
